 Table 1) (
 
  16
 ). Partial small (S) segment sequences (which encode the nucleocapsid protein [N]) of SEOV (nt 584–1019) were amplified with primers HV-SFO and HV-SRO for initial PCR (
 
  17
 ) and with primers SEO-SF and SEOV-SR (
 
  18
 ) for the second round of amplification, which yielded the 437-bp product (
 Table 1). For amplification of HTNV partial S segment sequences (nt 462–1025), primers HV-SFO and HV-SRO (
 
  17
 ) were used for initial PCR, and primers HSF and HSR (
 
  18
 ) were used for nested PCR, which amplifies the 564-bp product.
